Document: CollisionObject2D
Path: godot/classes/class_collisionobject2d.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties of CollisionObject2D, including collision layers, masks, priority, disable mode, and input pickability.

Property Descriptions

*   **collision_layer** (int): The physics layers this CollisionObject2D is in. Collision objects can exist in one or more of 32 different layers. See also collision_mask. Default: 1.
    Note: Object A can detect a contact with object B only if object B is in any of the layers that object A scans.
    Method: set_collision_layer(value: int)
    Method: get_collision_layer() → int

*   **collision_mask** (int): The physics layers this CollisionObject2D scans. Collision objects can scan one or more of 32 different layers. See also collision_layer. Default: 1.
    Note: Object A can detect a contact with object B only if object B is in any of the layers that object A scans.
    Method: set_collision_mask(value: int)
    Method: get_collision_mask() → int

*   **collision_priority** (float): The priority used to solve colliding when occurring penetration. The higher the priority is, the lower the penetration into the object will be. This can for example be used to prevent the player from breaking through the boundaries of a level. Default: 1.0.
    Method: set_collision_priority(value: float)
    Method: get_collision_priority() → float

*   **disable_mode** (DisableMode): Defines the behavior in physics when Node.process_mode is set to Node.PROCESS_MODE_DISABLED. Default: 0.
    Method: set_disable_mode(value: DisableMode)
    Method: get_disable_mode() → DisableMode

*   **input_pickable** (bool): If true, this object is pickable. A pickable object can detect the mouse pointer entering/leaving, and if the mouse is inside it, report input events. Requires at least one collision_layer bit to be set. Default: true.
    Method: set_pickable(value: bool)
    Method: is_pickable() → bool
